Following the abduction of students of the Government Science College Kagara by bandits, the National Security Adviser, Babagana Munguno, the Inspector General of Police, Adamu Mohammed, the Minister of Police have arrived Niger state to set the victims free.  This development was disclosed by Bashir Ahmad, the personal assistant to President Buhari on Media and Publicity. The Tweet Reads; ”The National Security Adviser (NSA), IG of Police, Interior, Information and Police Affairs Ministers are currently in Minna, Niger State as part of the Federal Government rescue operations of students of the Government Science College, Kagara, abducted by bandits last night.” Abubakar Sani Bello, the Governor of Niger State, has said his administration will not pay ransom to kidnappers, The PUNCH reports. Bello said this following the abduction of some students and staff of Government Science College in Kangara, Rafi Local Government Area of Niger State in the early hours of… In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate Wednesday called on President Muhammadu Buhari, to as a matter of urgency, declare a state of emergency on insecurity in the country. This was just as the Upper Chamber condemned in very strong terms, Wednesday’s abduction of students and teachers of Government… In "Top Stories" President Muhammadu Buhari has been asked by the Senate on Wednesday, February 17 to declare a state of emergency on insecurity following the abduction of students in Niger State by bandits. The red chamber made the call following a point of order by Senator Sani Musa (APC, Niger East), on… In "News"